    <string name="task_guide_toc_title">Contents</string>
    <string name="task_guide_section_features">Feature Guide</string>
    <string name="task_guide_section_howto">How to Use</string>
    <string name="task_guide_app_intro_title">App Overview</string>
    <string name="task_guide_app_intro_body">The EoD task manager helps you plan, record, review, and receive reminders for regular and irregular work by vessel. The usual flow is to prepare a preset for repeated work, connect that preset to the vessel you use, then record work by date as needed.</string>
    <string name="task_guide_main_features_title">Main Features</string>
    <string name="task_guide_main_features_body">The task manager provides the functions below so you can prepare regular work first and then record daily work quickly and consistently.</string>
    <string name="task_guide_feature_home_title">Home Screen</string>
    <string name="task_guide_feature_home_body">From the home screen you can open Task Manager, Port, Cargo, and the other main tools.</string>
    <string name="task_guide_feature_task_main_title">Task Manager Main Screen</string>
    <string name="task_guide_feature_task_main_body">From the main task screen you can move to vessels, alarm list, presets, and data management.</string>
    <string name="task_guide_feature_preset_title">Create Presets</string>
    <string name="task_guide_feature_preset_body">A preset is the setup unit used to manage several regular work items together. You can create, rename, delete, and activate presets.</string>
    <string name="task_guide_feature_regular_work_title">Register Regular Work</string>
    <string name="task_guide_feature_regular_work_body">Inside a preset you can register repeated work with a work name, procedure or reference, cycle number, and cycle unit.</string>
    <string name="task_guide_feature_vessel_title">Register and Activate Vessels</string>
    <string name="task_guide_feature_vessel_body">You can add, rename, delete, and activate vessels. Only one vessel can be active at a time.</string>
    <string name="task_guide_feature_record_home_title">Work Record Home</string>
    <string name="task_guide_feature_record_home_body">The work record home shows the calendar, date summary, and the work list for the selected date.</string>
    <string name="task_guide_feature_record_write_title">Write Work Records</string>
    <string name="task_guide_feature_record_write_body">For regular work you load a preset item. For irregular work you enter the work name directly. You can record the work name, reference, cycle, status, comment, and attachments.</string>
    <string name="task_guide_feature_recent_title">View Recent Records</string>
    <string name="task_guide_feature_recent_body">You can open recent records of the same work to review previous details before writing or editing a record.</string>
    <string name="task_guide_feature_record_list_title">Work List Screen</string>
    <string name="task_guide_feature_record_list_body">This screen shows records for a selected date or across the full period. You can search, change status, and reopen saved records.</string>
    <string name="task_guide_feature_alarm_list_title">Alarm List</string>
    <string name="task_guide_feature_alarm_list_body">The alarm list lets you turn all alarms on or off, turn each work alarm on or off, and check both regular and irregular work alarms.</string>
    <string name="task_guide_feature_alarm_time_title">Alarm Time</string>
    <string name="task_guide_feature_alarm_time_body">The alarm time is stored in 24-hour format and is used as the standard time for task alarms.</string>
    <string name="task_guide_feature_data_manage_title">Data Management</string>
    <string name="task_guide_feature_data_manage_body">You can import and export presets, reset presets, reset work records, or reset task manager app data.</string>
    <string name="task_guide_feature_attachment_title">Attachments</string>
    <string name="task_guide_feature_attachment_body">You can attach photos and videos, preview them, delete them, and restore them when you open the saved record again.</string>
    <string name="task_guide_alarm_explanation_title">Alarm Function</string>
    <string name="task_guide_alarm_explanation_body">To receive alarms, all alarms must be on, the individual work alarm must be on, a real work record must be saved, and the alarm time must be set. Day work alarms are sent on the due day, Week alarms one day before and on the day, Month alarms five days before and on the day, and Year alarms ten days before and on the day. Irregular work uses same-day alarm rules.</string>
    <string name="task_guide_screen_summary_title">Screen Summary</string>
    <string name="task_guide_screen_summary_body">Home opens Task Manager. The main task screen opens vessels, alarms, presets, and data management. Preset screens manage preset data. Work record home checks dates and lists. The record editor writes or updates work records. The list screen reviews records by date or full period. The alarm screen controls alarm use and time. Data management handles import, export, and reset.</string>
    <string name="task_guide_howto_first_title">When Using It for the First Time</string>
    <string name="task_guide_howto_first_body">Open Task Manager, create a preset, register the regular work inside it, activate the preset, add or choose a vessel, activate that vessel, and then tap the vessel to enter the work record home.</string>
    <string name="task_guide_howto_regular_title">How to Prepare Regular Work</string>
    <string name="task_guide_howto_regular_body">Regular work should be prepared in a preset first. Register each repeated work item with its name, reference or procedure, and cycle so that it can be loaded quickly later.</string>
    <string name="task_guide_howto_write_title">How to Record Actual Work</string>
    <string name="task_guide_howto_write_body">After activating a vessel, tap the vessel to open the work record home, select a date, and press the pencil button to write a new record. For regular work, tap the work field, choose Regular, select the saved work, fill in the status and details, and save. For irregular work, tap the work field, choose Irregular, enter the work name directly, fill in the status and details, and save.</string>
    <string name="task_guide_howto_date_title">How to Check by Date</string>
    <string name="task_guide_howto_date_body">Select a date on the calendar and review the work list below. Tap the same date again to open the more detailed work list for that date.</string>
    <string name="task_guide_howto_edit_title">How to Edit Previous Records</string>
    <string name="task_guide_howto_edit_body">Tap a record in the work list, change the details in the record editor, and save again. You can also use the recent record view to review older records of the same work.</string>
    <string name="task_guide_howto_alarm_title">How to Use Alarms</string>
    <string name="task_guide_howto_alarm_body">Open the alarm list, turn on all alarms, set the alarm time, and then turn on the individual work alarms you need. After that, alarms are sent according to the work cycle rules.</string>
    <string name="task_guide_howto_irregular_title">How to Manage Irregular Work</string>
    <string name="task_guide_howto_irregular_body">Irregular work is used for work that was not prepared in advance. You can directly enter unexpected inspections, temporary checks, or additional requests and manage them in the same record flow.</string>
    <string name="task_guide_howto_data_manage_title">How to Use Data Management</string>
    <string name="task_guide_howto_data_manage_body">Use data management when you want to back up or move presets. Import brings back saved preset files, export saves the current preset to a file, and reset removes saved data according to the selected range.</string>
    <string name="task_guide_howto_flow_title">Recommended Flow</string>
    <string name="task_guide_howto_flow_body">Create presets, register regular work, activate a preset, add or select a vessel, activate the vessel, enter the work record home, record regular or irregular work, turn on alarms when needed, review by date, and export or reset data when necessary.</string>
